    "recap_headline": "University of Connecticut Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SAN JOSE\n- The UConn\u00a0baseball team (12-13) completed a doubleheader sweep on Sunday with a 7-5 victory against San Diego State and a shutout, 8-0, win against San Jose State on a hot, sunny Sunday afternoon.\nThe Huskies utilized three home runs in game one including a pair of two-run home runs from junior captain\nTyler Minick\nin the first game of the twin bill.\nMinick put the Huskies ahead with a two-run homer in the third inning.\nCam Righi\nfollowed with solo shot as the Huskies hit back-to-back homers for the second-straight day.\nLeading 3-2 in the fifth,\nSteve Thomas\ndelivered a two-out, two-run single to give UConn a bit of breathing room. After the Aztecs responded with two runs in the sixth, Minick hit his second long ball of the day to push the lead to 7-4.\nLHP\nOliver Pudvar\nearned the victory working into the sixth inning on Sunday and\nGreg Shaw III\nwas an important bridge to keep the Huskies ahead. Shaw got out of a bases-loaded, no-out jam in the seventh with just allowing one run to keep UConn ahead, 7-5.\nCharlie Hale\nclosed the game out with a scoreless ninth to earn his first save of the year.\nHale then started game two and earned the victory on the bump. The RHP 6.1 shutout innings with just three hits allowed.\nThe game stayed tied 0-0 until the sixth when the Huskies tied their highest scoring inning of the season with eight runs coming across.\nChase Taylor\nand\nRob Rispoli\nstarted the rally with back-to-back singles to start the frame.\nMInick lined a two-run single to right to give UConn to 2-0 advantage.\nMaddix Dalena\ncame up with the big hit to provide insurance with a two-run double to the left center field alley.\nPaxton Meyers\nclosed out the win with 2.2 shutout innings and secured the Huskies second shutout of the season.",
